   <p><em>Note: This episode originally ran in <a href="http://www.npr.org/sections/money/2015/09/25/443519599/episode-653-the-anti-store" target="_blank">2015</a>.</em></p>   <p>It used to be that if you ran a store, you wanted to make it easy for your customers. But Price Club and Costco went in the opposite direction: They made shopping harder. And people loved it.</p>   <p>Today on the show: How Costco and its imitators changed the way we shop. And how a new company is taking what Costco started to new extremes.</p>   <p><em>Music: "</em><a href="https://www.firstcom.com/#!/results.aspx?pageNo=1&resultsPerPage=20&viewTags=1&mode=work&sortFilter=Default%7CDesc&keyword=708566&keywordType=1"><em>Heatwave</em></a><em>." </em><em>Find us: </em><a href="http://twitter.com/planetmoney" target="_blank"><em>Twitter</em></a><em>/ </em><a href="http://www.facebook.com/home.php?ref=home#%21/planetmoney?ref=ts" target="_blank"><em>Facebook</em></a><em>.</em></p>   <p><em>Subscribe to our show on </em><a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/planet-money/id290783428?mt=2" target="_blank"><em>Apple Podcasts</em></a><em> or </em><a href="http://pca.st/planetmoney" target="_blank"><em>PocketCast</em></a><em>.</em></p>
